msgid "Signal"
msgstr "Comhartha"

msgid "Using signals"
msgstr "Comharthaí a úsáid"

msgid ""
"In this lesson, we will look at signals. They are messages that nodes emit "
"when something specific happens to them, like a button being pressed. Other "
"nodes can connect to that signal and call a function when the event occurs."
msgstr ""
"Sa cheacht seo, féachfaimid ar chomharthaí. Is teachtaireachtaí iad a "
"astaíonn nóid nuair a tharlaíonn rud éigin sonrach dóibh, cosúil le cnaipe á "
"bhrú. Is féidir le nóid eile nascadh leis an gcomhartha sin agus feidhm a "
"ghlaoch nuair a tharlaíonn an ócáid."

msgid ""
"Signals are a delegation mechanism built into Godot that allows one game "
"object to react to a change in another without them referencing one another. "
"Using signals limits `coupling <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/"
"Coupling_(computer_programming)>`_ and keeps your code flexible."
msgstr ""
"Meicníocht tarmligin is ea comharthaí atá ionsuite i Godot a ligeann do réad "
"cluiche amháin freagairt d’athrú i gceann eile gan tagairt a dhéanamh dá "
"chéile. Trí chomharthaí a úsáid cuirtear teorainn le `cúpláil <https://"
"en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coupling_(computer_programming)>`_ agus coinníonn sé "
"do chód solúbtha."

msgid ""
"For example, you might have a life bar on the screen that represents the "
"player's health. When the player takes damage or uses a healing potion, you "
"want the bar to reflect the change. To do so, in Godot, you would use "
"signals."
msgstr ""
"Mar shampla, b'fhéidir go mbeadh barra saoil agat ar an scáileán a léiríonn "
"sláinte an imreora. Nuair a ghlacann an t-imreoir damáiste nó nuair a "
"úsáideann sé potion cneasaithe, ba mhaith leat go léireoidh an barra an t-"
"athrú. Chun é sin a dhéanamh, i Godot, úsáideann tú comharthaí."

msgid ""
"Like methods (:ref:`class_callable`), signals are a first-class type since "
"Godot 4.0. This means you can pass them around as method arguments directly "
"without having to pass them as strings, which allows for better "
"autocompletion and is less error-prone. See the :ref:`class_signal` class "
"reference for a list of what you can do with the Signal type directly."
msgstr ""
"Cosúil le modhanna (:ref: `class_callable`), is cineál den chéad scoth iad "
"comharthaí ó Godot 4.0. Ciallaíonn sé seo gur féidir leat iad a chur "
"timpeall mar argóintí modh go díreach gan iad a rith mar teaghráin, rud a "
"cheadaíonn uathchomhlánú níos fearr agus nach bhfuil níos lú seans ann ó "
"earráidí. Féach an tagairt aicme:ref: `class_signal` le haghaidh liosta de "
"na rudaí is féidir leat a dhéanamh leis an gcineál Comhartha go díreach."

msgid ""
"As mentioned in the introduction, signals are Godot's version of the "
"observer pattern. You can learn more about it in `Game Programming Patterns "
"<https://gameprogrammingpatterns.com/observer.html>`__."
msgstr ""
"Mar a luadh sa réamhrá, is ionann comharthaí agus leagan Godot den phatrún "
"breathnadóireachta. Is féidir leat níos mó a fhoghlaim faoi i `Game "
"Programming Patterns <https://gameprogrammingpatterns.com/observer.html>`__."

msgid ""
"We will now use a signal to make our Godot icon from the previous lesson "
"(:ref:`doc_scripting_player_input`) move and stop by pressing a button."
msgstr ""
"Úsáidfimid comhartha anois chun ár ndeilbhín Godot ón gceacht roimhe seo "
"(:ref: `doc_scripting_player_input`) a bhogadh agus a stopadh trí chnaipe a "
"bhrú."

msgid "For this project, we will be following the Godot naming conventions."
msgstr ""
"Maidir leis an tionscadal seo, beimid ag leanúint coinbhinsiúin ainmnithe "
"Godot."

msgid ""
"**GDScript**: Classes (nodes) use PascalCase, variables and functions use "
"snake_case, and constants use ALL_CAPS (See :ref:`doc_gdscript_styleguide`)."
msgstr ""
"**GDScript**: Úsáideann ranganna (nóid) PascalCase, úsáideann athróga agus "
"feidhmeanna snake_case, agus úsáideann comhsheasmhainí ALL_CAPS (féach: ref: "
"`doc_gdscript_styleguide`)."

msgid ""
"**C#**: Classes, export variables and methods use PascalCase, private fields "
"use _camelCase, local variables and parameters use camelCase "
"(See :ref:`doc_c_sharp_styleguide`). Be careful to type the method names "
"precisely when connecting signals."
msgstr ""
"**C#**: Úsáideann aicmí, athróga easpórtála agus modhanna PascalCase, "
"úsáideann réimsí príobháideacha _camelCase, úsáideann athróga áitiúla agus "
"paraiméadair camelCase (Féach :ref:`doc_c_sharp_styleguide`). Bí cúramach "
"ainmneacha na modhanna a chlóscríobh go beacht agus tú ag nascadh comharthaí."

msgid "Scene setup"
msgstr "Socrú radharc"

msgid ""
"To add a button to our game, we will create a new scene which will include "
"both a :ref:`Button <class_button>` and the ``sprite_2d.tscn`` scene we "
"created in the :ref:`doc_scripting_first_script` lesson."
msgstr ""
"Chun cnaipe a chur lenár gcluiche, cruthóimid radharc nua a chuimseoidh an "
"dá radharc :ref:`Button <class_button>` agus an radharc `` sprite_2d.tscn`` "
"a chruthaigh muid sa cheacht :ref:`doc_scripting_first_script`."

msgid "Create a new scene by going to the menu Scene -> New Scene."
msgstr ""
"Cruthaigh radharc nua trí dul go dtí an Radharc roghchlár -> Radharc Nua."

msgid ""
"In the Scene dock, click the 2D Scene button. This will add a :ref:`Node2D "
"<class_Node2D>` as our root."
msgstr ""
"Sa duga Radharc, cliceáil ar an gcnaipe Radharc 2D. Cuirfidh sé "
"seo :ref:`Node2D <class_Node2D>` mar ár bhfréamh."

msgid ""
"In the FileSystem dock, click and drag the ``sprite_2d.tscn`` file you saved "
"previously onto the Node2D to instantiate it."
msgstr ""
"Sa duga Córais FileCórais, cliceáil agus tarraing an comhad "
"``sprite_2d.tscn`` a shábháil tú roimhe seo ar an Node2D chun é a chur "
"isteach."

msgid ""
"We want to add another node as a sibling of the Sprite2D. To do so, right-"
"click on Node2D and select Add Child Node."
msgstr ""
"Ba mhaith linn nód eile a chur leis mar dheirfiúr den Sprite2D. Chun é sin a "
"dhéanamh, cliceáil ar dheis ar Node2D agus roghnaigh Cuir Nód Leanaí leis."

msgid "Search for the :ref:`Button <class_button>` node and add it."
msgstr "Cuardaigh an nód :ref:`Button <class_button>` agus cuir leis é."

msgid ""
"The node is small by default. Click and drag on the bottom-right handle of "
"the Button in the viewport to resize it."
msgstr ""
"Tá an nód beag de réir réamhshocraithe. Cliceáil agus tarraing ar láimhseáil "
"bun ar dheis an Cnaipe sa radharc chun é a athrú."

msgid ""
"If you don't see the handles, ensure the select tool is active in the "
"toolbar."
msgstr ""
"Mura bhfeiceann tú na hanlaí, cinntigh go bhfuil an uirlis roghnaithe "
"gníomhach sa bharra uirlisí."

msgid "Click and drag on the button itself to move it closer to the sprite."
msgstr ""
"Cliceáil agus tarraing ar an gcnaipe féin chun é a bhogadh níos gaire don "
"sprite."

msgid ""
"You can also write a label on the Button by editing its Text property in the "
"Inspector. Enter ``Toggle motion``."
msgstr ""
"Is féidir leat lipéad a scríobh ar an gCnaipe freisin trí a mhaoin Téacs a "
"chur in eagar sa Cigire. Cuir isteach ``Toggle ghluaise``."

msgid "Your scene tree and viewport should look like this."
msgstr "Ba chóir go mbeadh cuma seo ar do chrann radhairc agus do radharc."

msgid ""
"Save your newly created scene as ``node_2d.tscn``, if you haven't already. "
"You can then run it with :kbd:`F6` (:kbd:`Cmd + R` on macOS). At the moment, "
"the button will be visible, but nothing will happen if you press it."
msgstr ""
"Sábháil do radharc nua-chruthaithe mar ``node_2d.tscn``, mura bhfuil tú "
"cheana féin. Ansin is féidir leat é a rith le: kbd: `F6` (:kbd: `Cmd + R` ar "
"macOS). I láthair na huaire, beidh an cnaipe le feiceáil, ach ní tharlóidh "
"aon rud má bhrúiteann tú é."

msgid "Connecting a signal in the editor"
msgstr "Comhartha a nascadh san eagarthóir"

msgid ""
"Here, we want to connect the Button's \"pressed\" signal to our Sprite2D, "
"and we want to call a new function that will toggle its motion on and off. "
"We need to have a script attached to the Sprite2D node, which we do from the "
"previous lesson."
msgstr ""
"Anseo, ba mhaith linn comhartha “brúite” an Chnaipe a nascadh lenár "
"Sprite2D, agus ba mhaith linn feidhm nua a ghlaoch a ghlaoch a ghluaiseacht "
"air agus as. Ní mór dúinn script a bheith ceangailte leis an nód Sprite2D, a "
"dhéanaimid ón gceacht roimhe seo."

msgid ""
"You can connect signals in the Node dock. Select the Button node and, on the "
"right side of the editor, click on the tab named \"Node\" next to the "
"Inspector."
msgstr ""
"Is féidir leat comharthaí a nascadh sa duga Nóid. Roghnaigh an nód Cnaipe "
"agus, ar thaobh na láimhe deise den eagarthóir, cliceáil ar an gcluaisín "
"darb ainm “Nód” in aice leis an gCigire."

msgid "The dock displays a list of signals available on the selected node."
msgstr ""
"Taispeánann an duga liosta de na comharthaí atá ar fáil ar an nód roghnaithe."

msgid "Double-click the \"pressed\" signal to open the node connection window."
msgstr ""
"Cliceáil faoi dhó ar an comhartha \"brúite\" chun an fhuinneog nasc nód a "
"oscailt."

msgid ""
"There, you can connect the signal to the Sprite2D node. The node needs a "
"receiver method, a function that Godot will call when the Button emits the "
"signal. The editor generates one for you. By convention, we name these "
"callback methods \"_on_node_name_signal_name\". Here, it'll be "
"\"_on_button_pressed\"."
msgstr ""
"Ansin, is féidir leat an comhartha a nascadh leis an nód Sprite2D. "
"Teastaíonn modh glacadóra ón nód, feidhm a ghlaoidh Godot nuair a astaíonn "
"an Cnaipe an comhartha. Gineann an t-eagarthóir ceann duit. De réir "
"choinbhinsiúin, ainmnímid na modhanna aisghlaonna seo "
"“_on_node_name_signal_name”. Anseo, beidh sé “_on_button_pressed”."

msgid ""
"When connecting signals via the editor's Node dock, you can use two modes. "
"The simple one only allows you to connect to nodes that have a script "
"attached to them and creates a new callback function on them."
msgstr ""
"Agus comharthaí á nascadh trí duga Nód an eagarthóra, is féidir leat dhá "
"mhodh a úsáid. Ní cheadaíonn an ceann simplí duit ach ceangal le nóid a "
"bhfuil script ceangailte leo agus cruthaíonn sé feidhm nua glaonna ar ais "
"orthu."

msgid ""
"The advanced view lets you connect to any node and any built-in function, "
"add arguments to the callback, and set options. You can toggle the mode in "
"the window's bottom-right by clicking the Advanced button."
msgstr ""
"Ligeann an dearcadh chun cinn duit nascadh le haon nód agus le haon fheidhm "
"ionsuite, argóintí a chur leis an aisghlao, agus roghanna a shocrú. Is "
"féidir leat an modh a athrú i mbun ar dheis na fuinneoige trí chliceáil ar "
"an gcnaipe Advanced."

msgid ""
"Click the Connect button to complete the signal connection and jump to the "
"Script workspace. You should see the new method with a connection icon in "
"the left margin."
msgstr ""
"Cliceáil ar an gcnaipe Ceangail chun an nasc comhartha a chríochnú agus léim "
"chuig an spás oibre Script. Ba chóir duit an modh nua a fheiceáil le "
"deilbhín nasc san imeall ar chlé."

msgid ""
"If you click the icon, a window pops up and displays information about the "
"connection. This feature is only available when connecting nodes in the "
"editor."
msgstr ""
"Má chliceálann tú ar an deilbhín, tagann fuinneog suas agus taispeánann tú "
"faisnéis faoin nasc. Níl an ghné seo ar fáil ach amháin nuair a bhíonn nóid "
"á nascadh san eagarthóir."

msgid ""
"Let's replace the line with the ``pass`` keyword with code that'll toggle "
"the node's motion."
msgstr ""
"Cuirimid an eochairfhocal ``pas ``in ionad an líne le cód a thiocfaidh "
"gluaiseacht an nód."

msgid ""
"Our Sprite2D moves thanks to code in the ``_process()`` function. Godot "
"provides a method to toggle processing on and off: :ref:`Node.set_process() "
"<class_Node_method_set_process>`. Another method of the Node class, "
"``is_processing()``, returns ``true`` if idle processing is active. We can "
"use the ``not`` keyword to invert the value."
msgstr ""
"Bogann ár Sprite2D a bhuíochas le cód san fheidhm ``_process()``. "
"Soláthraíonn Godot modh chun próiseáil a scoránaigh ar agus "
"as: :ref:`Node.set_process() <class_Node_method_set_process>`. Tugann modh "
"eile den aicme Nód, ``is_processing()``, ``fíor`` ar ais má tá próiseáil "
"díomhaoin gníomhach. Is féidir linn an eochairfhocal ``not`` a úsáid chun an "
"luach a inbhéartú."

msgid ""
"This function will toggle processing and, in turn, the icon's motion on and "
"off upon pressing the button."
msgstr ""
"Déanfaidh an fheidhm seo próiseáil a athrú agus, ina dhiaidh sin, "
"gluaiseacht an deilbhín air agus as ar an gcnaipe a bhrú."

msgid ""
"Before trying the game, we need to simplify our ``_process()`` function to "
"move the node automatically and not wait for user input. Replace it with the "
"following code, which we saw two lessons ago:"
msgstr ""
"Sula ndéanaimid triail as an gcluiche, ní mór dúinn ár bhfeidhm ``_process "
"() `a shimpliú chun an nód a bhogadh go huathoibríoch agus gan fanacht le "
"hionchur úsáideora. Cuir an cód seo a leanas in ionad é, a chonaic muid dhá "
"cheacht ó shin:"

msgid "Your complete ``sprite_2d.gd`` code should look like the following."
msgstr ""
"Ba chóir go mbeadh cuma mar seo a leanas ar do chód iomlán ``sprite_2d.gd``."

msgid "Connecting a signal via code"
msgstr "Comhartha a nascadh trí chód"

msgid ""
"You can connect signals via code instead of using the editor. This is "
"necessary when you create nodes or instantiate scenes inside of a script."
msgstr ""
"Is féidir leat comharthaí a nascadh trí chód in ionad an eagarthóir a úsáid. "
"Tá sé seo riachtanach nuair a chruthaíonn tú nóid nó nuair a chruthaíonn tú "
"radhairc taobh istigh de script."

msgid ""
"Let's use a different node here. Godot has a :ref:`Timer <class_Timer>` node "
"that's useful to implement skill cooldown times, weapon reloading, and more."
msgstr ""
"A ligean ar úsáid a bhaint as nód eile anseo. Tá nód :ref:`Timer "
"<class_Timer>` ag Godot atá úsáideach chun amanna fuarú scileanna, athlódáil "
"arm agus go leor eile a chur i bhfeidhm."

msgid ""
"Head back to the 2D workspace. You can either click the \"2D\" text at the "
"top of the window or press :kbd:`Ctrl + F1` (:kbd:`Ctrl + Cmd + 1` on macOS)."
msgstr ""
"Téigh ar ais go dtí an spás oibre 2D. Is féidir leat cliceáil ar an téacs "
"“2D” ag barr na fuinneoige nó brúite:kbd: `Ctrl + F1` (:kbd: `Ctrl + Cmd + "
"1` ar macOS)."

msgid ""
"In the Scene dock, right-click on the Sprite2D node and add a new child "
"node. Search for Timer and add the corresponding node. Your scene should now "
"look like this."
msgstr ""
"Sa duga Radhairc, cliceáil ar dheis ar an nód Sprite2D agus cuir nód leanbh "
"nua leis. Cuardaigh Timer agus cuir an nód comhfhreagrach leis. Ba chóir go "
"mbeadh cuma seo ar do radharc anois."

msgid ""
"With the Timer node selected, go to the Inspector and enable the "
"**Autostart** property."
msgstr ""
"Agus an nód Timer roghnaithe, téigh chuig an gCigire agus cumasaigh an "
"maoine **Autostart**."

msgid ""
"Click the script icon next to Sprite2D to jump back to the scripting "
"workspace."
msgstr ""
"Cliceáil an deilbhín script in aice le Sprite2D chun léim ar ais go dtí an "
"spás oibre scripteála."

msgid "We need to do two operations to connect the nodes via code:"
msgstr "Ní mór dúinn dhá oibríocht a dhéanamh chun na nóid a nascadh trí chód:"

msgid "Get a reference to the Timer from the Sprite2D."
msgstr "Faigh tagairt don Timer ón Sprite2D."

msgid "Call the ``connect()`` method on the Timer's \"timeout\" signal."
msgstr ""
"Glaoigh ar an modh ``connect () ``ar chomhartha “ama amach” an Uaimeora."

msgid ""
"To connect to a signal via code, you need to call the ``connect()`` method "
"of the signal you want to listen to. In this case, we want to listen to the "
"Timer's \"timeout\" signal."
msgstr ""
"Chun nascadh le comhartha trí chód, ní mór duit glaoch ar an modh ``connect "
"() ``den chomhartha a theastaíonn uait éisteacht leis. Sa chás seo, ba "
"mhaith linn éisteacht le comhartha “ama amach” an Timer."

msgid ""
"We want to connect the signal when the scene is instantiated, and we can do "
"that using the :ref:`Node._ready() <class_Node_private_method__ready>` built-"
"in function, which is called automatically by the engine when a node is "
"fully instantiated."
msgstr ""
"Ba mhaith linn an comhartha a nascadh nuair a bhíonn an radharc ar an toirt, "
"agus is féidir linn é sin a dhéanamh ag baint úsáide as "
"an :ref:`Node._ready() <class_Node_private_method__ready>` feidhm ionsuite, "
"a ghlaoitear go huathoibríoch ag an inneall nuair a bhíonn nód ar an toirt "
"go hiomlán ."

msgid ""
"To get a reference to a node relative to the current one, we use the "
"method :ref:`Node.get_node() <class_Node_method_get_node>`. We can store the "
"reference in a variable."
msgstr ""
"Chun tagairt a fháil do nód i gcoibhneas leis an gceann reatha, úsáidimid an "
"modh :ref:`Node.get_node() <class_Node_method_get_node>`. Is féidir linn an "
"tagairt a stóráil in athróg."

msgid ""
"The function ``get_node()`` looks at the Sprite2D's children and gets nodes "
"by their name. For example, if you renamed the Timer node to "
"\"BlinkingTimer\" in the editor, you would have to change the call to "
"``get_node(\"BlinkingTimer\")``."
msgstr ""
"Breathnaíonn an fheidhm ``get_node () ``ar pháistí an Sprite2D agus "
"faigheann sé nóid dá n-ainm. Mar shampla, má athainmníodh tú an nód Timer go "
"“BlinkingTimer” san eagarthóir, bheadh ort an glao a athrú go ``get_node "
"(“BlinkingTimer”) ``."

msgid ""
"We can now connect the Timer to the Sprite2D in the ``_ready()`` function."
msgstr ""
"Is féidir linn anois an Timer a nascadh leis an Sprite2D sa fheidhm ``_ready "
"() ``."

msgid ""
"The line reads like so: we connect the Timer's \"timeout\" signal to the "
"node to which the script is attached. When the Timer emits ``timeout``, we "
"want to call the function ``_on_timer_timeout()``, that we need to define. "
"Let's add it at the bottom of our script and use it to toggle our sprite's "
"visibility."
msgstr ""
"Léann an líne mar sin: nascann muid comhartha “ama amach” an Timer leis an "
"nód lena bhfuil an script ceangailte leis. Nuair a astaíonn an Timer "
"``timeout``, ba mhaith linn glaoch ar an bhfeidhm ``_on_timer_timeout () ``, "
"a chaithfimid a shainiú. Cuirimid é ag bun ár script agus bain úsáid as chun "
"infheictheacht ár sprite a athrú."

msgid ""
"By convention, we name these callback methods in GDScript as "
"\"_on_node_name_signal_name\" and in C# as \"OnNodeNameSignalName\". Here, "
"it'll be \"_on_timer_timeout\" for GDScript and OnTimerTimeout() for C#."
msgstr ""
"De réir choinbhinsiúin, ainmnímid na modhanna aisghlaonna seo i GDScript mar "
"“_on_node_name_signal_name” agus i C # mar “OnNodeNameSignalName”. Anseo, "
"beidh sé “_on_timer_timeout” do GDScript agus OnTimerTimeout () do C #."

msgid ""
"The ``visible`` property is a boolean that controls the visibility of our "
"node. The line ``visible = not visible`` toggles the value. If ``visible`` "
"is ``true``, it becomes ``false``, and vice-versa."
msgstr ""
"Is boolean í an maoin `infheictheach`` a rialaíonn infheictheacht ár nód. "
"Athraíonn an líne ``infheicthe = nach bhfuil feiceáil`` an luach. Má tá "
"``infheictheach`` `fíor``, éiríonn sé ``bréag``, agus a mhalairt."

msgid ""
"If you run the Node2D scene now, you will see that the sprite blinks on and "
"off, at one second intervals."
msgstr ""
"Má reáchtáil tú radharc Node2D anois, feicfidh tú go dtagann an sprite air "
"agus as, ag eatraimh soicind amháin."

msgid "Complete script"
msgstr "Script iomlán"

msgid ""
"That's it for our little moving and blinking Godot icon demo! Here is the "
"complete ``sprite_2d.gd`` file for reference."
msgstr ""
"Sin é dár dtaispeántas beag deilbhín Godot atá ag gluaiseacht agus ag "
"blacadh! Seo an comhad iomlán ``sprite_2d.gd`` le haghaidh tagartha."

msgid "Custom signals"
msgstr "Comharthaí saincheaptha"

msgid ""
"This section is a reference on how to define and use your own signals, and "
"does not build upon the project created in previous lessons."
msgstr ""
"Is tagairt í an chuid seo maidir le conas do chomharthaí féin a shainiú agus "
"a úsáid, agus ní thógann sé ar an tionscadal a cruthaíodh i gceachtanna "
"roimhe seo."

msgid ""
"You can define custom signals in a script. Say, for example, that you want "
"to show a game over screen when the player's health reaches zero. To do so, "
"you could define a signal named \"died\" or \"health_depleted\" when their "
"health reaches 0."
msgstr ""
"Is féidir leat comharthaí saincheaptha a shainiú i script. Abair, mar "
"shampla, gur mhaith leat cluiche a thaispeáint thar an scáileán nuair a "
"shroicheann sláinte an imreora nialas. Chun é sin a dhéanamh, d'fhéadfá "
"comhartha darb ainm “fuair bás” nó “health_ídithe” a shainiú nuair a "
"shroicheann a sláinte 0."

msgid ""
"As signals represent events that just occurred, we generally use an action "
"verb in the past tense in their names."
msgstr ""
"De réir mar a léiríonn comharthaí imeachtaí a tharla díreach, de ghnáth "
"úsáidimid briathar gníomhaíochta san am atá caite ina n-ainmneacha."

msgid ""
"Your signals work the same way as built-in ones: they appear in the Node tab "
"and you can connect to them like any other."
msgstr ""
"Oibríonn do chomharthaí ar an mbealach céanna le cinn ionsuite: tá siad le "
"feiceáil sa chluaisín Node agus is féidir leat nascadh leo cosúil le haon "
"cheann eile."

msgid "To emit a signal in your scripts, call ``emit()`` on the signal."
msgstr ""
"Chun comhartha a astú i do scripteanna, glaoigh ar ``emit()`` ar an "
"gcomhartha."

msgid ""
"A signal can optionally declare one or more arguments. Specify the argument "
"names between parentheses:"
msgstr ""
"Is féidir le comhartha argóint amháin nó níos mó a dhearbhú go roghnach. "
"Sonraigh na hainmneacha argóint idir lúibíní:"

msgid ""
"The signal arguments show up in the editor's node dock, and Godot can use "
"them to generate callback functions for you. However, you can still emit any "
"number of arguments when you emit signals. So it's up to you to emit the "
"correct values."
msgstr ""
"Taispeánann na hargóintí comhartha suas i nduga nód an eagarthóra, agus is "
"féidir le Godot iad a úsáid chun feidhmeanna glaonna aisghlaonna a ghiniúint "
"duit. Mar sin féin, is féidir leat líon ar bith argóintí a astú fós nuair a "
"astaíonn tú comharthaí. Mar sin is fútsa atá sé na luachanna cearta a "
"scaoileadh."

msgid ""
"To emit values along with the signal, add them as extra arguments to the "
"``emit()`` function:"
msgstr ""
"Chun luachanna a astú in éineacht leis an gcomhartha, cuir iad mar argóintí "
"breise leis an bhfeidhm ``emit ()``:"

msgid "Summary"
msgstr "Achoimre"

msgid ""
"Any node in Godot emits signals when something specific happens to them, "
"like a button being pressed. Other nodes can connect to individual signals "
"and react to selected events."
msgstr ""
"Astaíonn aon nód i Godot comharthaí nuair a tharlaíonn rud éigin sonrach "
"dóibh, cosúil le cnaipe á bhrú. Is féidir le nóid eile nascadh le comharthaí "
"aonair agus freagairt d'imeachtaí roghnaithe."

msgid ""
"Signals have many uses. With them, you can react to a node entering or "
"exiting the game world, to a collision, to a character entering or leaving "
"an area, to an element of the interface changing size, and much more."
msgstr ""
"Tá go leor úsáidí ag comharthaí. Leis leo, is féidir leat freagairt do nód a "
"théann isteach nó ag imeacht as domhan an chluiche, le imbhualadh, le "
"carachtar ag dul isteach nó ag fágáil limistéar, le heilimint den chomhéadan "
"ag athrú méid, agus go leor eile."

msgid ""
"For example, an :ref:`Area2D <class_Area2D>` representing a coin emits a "
"``body_entered`` signal whenever the player's physics body enters its "
"collision shape, allowing you to know when the player collected it."
msgstr ""
"Mar shampla, astaíonn :ref:`Area2D <class_Area2D>` a sheasann do bhonn "
"comhartha `` comhlacht_iontráil`` gach uair a théann corp fisice an imreora "
"isteach ina chruth imbhuailte, rud a ligeann duit fios a bheith agat cathain "
"a bhailigh an t-imreoir é."

msgid ""
"In the next section, :ref:`doc_your_first_2d_game`, you'll create a complete "
"2D game and put everything you learned so far into practice."
msgstr ""
"Sa chéad chuid eile, :ref: `doc_your_first_2d_game`, cruthóidh tú cluiche 2D "
"iomlán agus cuirfidh tú gach rud a d'fhoghlaim tú go dtí seo i bhfeidhm."
